get_mean <-function(m){

  for(i in 1:499){
  
    if(sp500names[i] == m){
    
      return(sp500means[i])

    } 

  } 
}


get_vars <-function(m){

  for(i in 1:499){
  
    if(sp500names[i] == m){
    
      return(sp500vars[i])

    } 

  } 
}

library(quantmod)
## Loading required package: xts
## Loading required package: zoo
## 
## Attaching package: 'zoo'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     as.Date, as.Date.numeric
## Loading required package: TTR
## Version 0.4-0 included new data defaults. See ?getSymbols.
big_number <- 124251

choices  <- read.table("paired_choices.txt", header=F)

proper_calculations <- matrix(NaN, big_number, 2, byrow=TRUE)
colnames(proper_calculations) <- c("value","variance")

omega_values <- vector(mode = "numeric", length = big_number)

golden_number <- big_number

# Download data


for(i in 1:golden_number){
  stock1 <- as.character(choices[i,1])
  stock2 <- as.character(choices[i,2])


# Get data from files
# get file names
temp_name1 <- paste(stock1,".txt")
file_stock1 <- gsub(" ", "", temp_name1)
temp_name2 <- paste(stock2,".txt")
file_stock2 <- gsub(" ", "", temp_name2)
  
# Compute returns
a <- na.omit(read.table(file_stock1, header=F))
n <- na.omit(read.table(file_stock2, header=F))



# Estimation of mu and Sigma
if(length(a[,1]) == length(n[,1])){
Sigma <- cov(cbind(a, n))#Sigma <- cov(cbind(get_vars(stock1), get_vars(stock2)))#
mu <- c(get_mean(stock1), get_mean(stock2))

# Compute omega^*
omega_star = (Sigma[2, 2] - Sigma[1, 2])/(Sigma[1, 1] + Sigma[2, 2] - 2*Sigma[1, 2])

# Compute investment expected value and variance
mu_investment = omega_star*mu[1] + (1 - omega_star)*mu[2]
var_investment = omega_star^2*Sigma[1,1] + (1 - omega_star)^2*Sigma[2,2] + 
  2*omega_star*(1 - omega_star)*Sigma[1,2]

#cat(i,stock1,stock2,"omega star",omega_star*100,"mu investment",mu_investment,"var investment",var_investment,"\n")
#print(choices[golden_number,])
proper_calculations[i,] <- c(mu_investment,var_investment)
omega_values[i] = omega_star
} else {
  print(i)
}
#cat(length(a[,1]),"and",length(n[,1]),"\n")

}
